data.text: Euro area monthly balance of payments (Sept 2016) https://t.co/lnRhl3KSeI
Draghi: We operate under a still significant degree of uncertainty; economic recovery also depends on other policy areas
Draghi: ECB will continue to act, as warranted, using all instruments available within mandate to secure inflation below but close to 2%
Draghi: Monetary policy remains a key ingredient in the reflation scenario we foresee in euro area in coming years
Draghi: 3 factors warrant caution: bank profitability, relative weakness of inflation dynamics and dependence of recovery on monetary policy
Draghi: Domestic strength has helped insulate the euro area against global weakness, which otherwise would have dragged recovery off track
Draghi: In banking regulation there should be no rolling back on what has been decided
Draghi: Regulatory measures should be implemented in a balanced way that ensures a global level playing field
Draghi: The focus of the regulatory agenda should be on implementation, not on new design
Draghi: Now is the time to finalise the regulatory agenda and enter a period of stability
Draghi: The re-regulation of the financial sector is part of the growth agenda - and major progress has now been made
Draghi: To be genuinely robust, the banking sector must be well-regulated
Draghi: A sustained adjustment in the path of inflation still relies on the continuation of the current, unprecedented financing conditions
